<subSubSection pageNumber="612" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="612">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="612">
Note: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="camara">Lantana camara</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, with the type designated by Moldenke &amp; Moldenke, was proposed as conserved type of the genus by Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="612">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 564. 1992). This was eventually approved by the General Committee (see review of the history of this proposal by Barrie, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="612">l.c.</emphasis>
55: 795-796. 2006). Sanders (in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="612">Sida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
22: 381-421. 2006) provided a detailed study of the type (illustrated on p. 384, f. 1), concluding that it belongs to the wild species and not to the cultigen to which the name has also been applied. As a result, he named the latter 
<taxonomicName authority="R. W. Sanders." authorityName="R.W. Sanders" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strigocamara">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="612">L. strigocamara</emphasis>
R.W. Sanders.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
